          " لَمْ تَتَوَاخَوْا عَلَى هَذَا الْأَمْرِ وَ إِنَّمَا تَعَارَفْتُمْ عَلَيْهِ ."
        ],
        "translations": {
          "en.hubeali": [
            "From him, from Ahmad Bin Muhammad, from Usman Bin Isa, from Ibn Muskan, and Sama’at, altogether, ",
            "(It has been narrated) from Abu Abdullah<sup style=\"font-weight: normal\">asws</sup> having said: ‘You are not yet establishing brotherhood upon this matter (Al-<span class=\"iTxt\">Wilayah</span>), but rather you are being recognised upon it’."
          ],
          "en.sarwar": [
            "2. It is narrated from him (narrator of the Hadith above) from Ahmad ibn Muhammad from ‘Uthman ibn ‘Isa from ibn Muskan and Sama’a all from abu ‘Abd Allah (a.s.) who has said the following: “You have not become brothers on the basis of this matter (Walayah the belief of the Shi’a Muslims); it is only that you have recognized each other by means of Walayah .” "
          ]
